  38. ‌int caml_addrmap_contains(struct addrmap* t, value key)
  39. {
  40.   uintnat pos, i;

  42.   CAMLassert(Is_block(key));
  43.   if (!t->entries) return 0;

  45.   for (i = 0, pos = pos_initial(t, key);
  46.        i < MAX_CHAIN;
  47.        i++, pos = pos_next(t, pos)) {
  48.     if (t->entries[pos].key == ADDRMAP_INVALID_KEY) break;
  49.     if (t->entries[pos].key == key) return 1;
  50.   }
  51.   return 0;
  52. }

  54. ‌value caml_addrmap_lookup(struct addrmap* t, value key)
  55. {
  56.   uintnat pos;

  58.   CAMLassert(Is_block(key));
  59.   CAMLassert(t->entries);

  61.   for (pos = pos_initial(t, key); ; pos = pos_next(t, pos)) {
  62.     CAMLassert(t->entries[pos].key != ADDRMAP_INVALID_KEY);
  63.     if (t->entries[pos].key == key)
  64.       return t->entries[pos].value;
  65.   }
  66. }

  68. ‌static void addrmap_alloc(struct addrmap* t, uintnat sz)
  69. {
  70.   uintnat i;
  71.   CAMLassert(Is_power_of_2(sz));
  72.   t->entries = caml_stat_alloc(sizeof(struct addrmap_entry) * sz);
  73.   t->size = sz;
  74.   for (i = 0; i < sz; i++) {
  75.     t->entries[i].key = ADDRMAP_INVALID_KEY;
  76.     t->entries[i].value = ADDRMAP_NOT_PRESENT;
  77.   }
  78. }

  93. ‌value* caml_addrmap_insert_pos(struct addrmap* t, value key) {
  94.   uintnat i, pos;
  95.   CAMLassert(Is_block(key));
  96.   if (!t->entries) {
  97.     /* first call, initialise table with a small initial size */
  98.     addrmap_alloc(t, 256);
  99.   }
  100.   for (i = 0, pos = pos_initial(t, key);
  101.        i < MAX_CHAIN;
  102.        i++,   pos = pos_next(t, pos)) {
  103.     if (t->entries[pos].key == ADDRMAP_INVALID_KEY) {
  104.       t->entries[pos].key = key;
  105.     }
  106.     if (t->entries[pos].key == key) {
  107.       return &t->entries[pos].value;
  108.     }
  109.   }
  110.   /* failed to insert, rehash and try again */
  111.   {
  112.     struct addrmap_entry* old_table = t->entries;
  113.     uintnat old_size = t->size;
  114.     addrmap_alloc(t, old_size * 2);
  115.     for (i = 0; i < old_size; i++) {
  116.       if (old_table[i].key != ADDRMAP_INVALID_KEY) {
  117.         value* p = caml_addrmap_insert_pos(t, old_table[i].key);
  118.         CAMLassert(*p == ADDRMAP_NOT_PRESENT);
  119.         *p = old_table[i].value;
  120.       }
  121.     }
  122.     caml_stat_free(old_table);
  123.   }
  124.   return caml_addrmap_insert_pos(t, key);
  125. }

  127. ‌void caml_addrmap_insert(struct addrmap* t, value k, value v) {
  128.   value* p = caml_addrmap_insert_pos(t, k);
  129.   CAMLassert(*p == ADDRMAP_NOT_PRESENT);
